Table A: Running EQ6 from EQ3/6-V8.0a (R43a) for PC
Description= 'React Halite and Gypsum to find the mutual solubility point'
This is part of the WIPP EQ3/6-FMT comparison study.
Add 10.0 moles of Halite (NaCl) and 1.0 mole of Gypsum (CaSO4.2H2O) to
'pure' water containing trace amounts of Na; K; Cl; and SO4. A reaction path
is calculated to achieve this. The objective is to find the invariant point
representing the mutual solubility of these two minerals. This problem
is a simplification of the original EQ3/6 test case gypnacl.6i. This problem
is closely analogous to those in the 'f24vc7' series that are also used in
Note that ClO4-; O2(aq); and H2(aq) are suppressed in the initializing
